<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDBFFB63FABFB04FD9CFB31" authority="Zerova, 1972: 1 - 6" authorityName="Zerova" authorityPageNumber="1 - 6" authorityYear="1972" box="[231,591,1233,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complanata">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDBFFB63FABFB04FE4EFB31" box="[231,413,1233,1255]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Systole complanata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B72FFDBFFB63EEFFB04FD9CFB31" author="Zerova, M. D." box="[419,591,1233,1255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" pagination="922 - 924" refId="ref3688" refString="Zerova, M. D. 1972. New Systole Walk. species from Middle Asia (Hymenoptera, Eurytomidae) Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 51 (6), 922 - 924 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1972">
Zerova, 1972: 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDBFFB63D60FB04FD9CFB31" box="[556,591,1233,1255]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">1–6</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
— female, paratype; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDBFFB63C57FB04FCF5FB31" box="[795,806,1233,1255]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">1</emphasis>
— adult, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDBFFB63CB2FB04FBDAFB31" box="[1022,1033,1233,1255]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">2</emphasis>
— head and thorax dorsally; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDBFFB63FB2FB39FECCFAD4" box="[254,287,1260,1282]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">3, 6</emphasis>
— antenna; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDBFFB63ED5FB39FE77FAD4" box="[409,420,1260,1282]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">4</emphasis>
— fore wing venation; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDBFFB63DCAFB39FD74FAD4" box="[646,679,1260,1282]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">5—</emphasis>
head, frontal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDBFFB63F97FA50FBD1F9F6" blockId="4.[166,1225,1317,1856]" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Mesosoma with flat dorsum; pronotal collar very short, almost 5.0 times as wide as long, and 2.0 times shorter than scutum, and almost as long as scutellum. Propodeum slightly sloping, wide and bulging on sides, with very thin, shallow sculpture. Forewing with short, but well-visible brown pubescence. Marginal vein as long as postmarginal vein; radial vein shorter than postmarginal, and with slightly elongated stigma.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDBFFB63F97F9F0FD71F9B6" blockId="4.[166,1225,1317,1856]" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Metasoma with short, but well-visible petiolus; abdomen shorter than head and mesosoma (in lateral view), without pubescence.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDBFFB63F97F9B0FE62F956" blockId="4.[166,1225,1317,1856]" box="[219,433,1637,1664]" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">M a l e not known.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
